  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "According to https://www.envoyproxy.io/docs/envoy/latest/configuration/http_conn_man/headers.html#x-b3-sampled the `X-B3-Sampled` flag is used to determine whether spans are reported, and the value is consistently propagated to downstream services.\r\n\r\nHowever currently it does not appear that this header is being used - and is set to always sample when [injecting the context in requests](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/master/source/common/tracing/zipkin/zipkin_tracer_impl.cc#L36).\r\n\r\nIs there any reason the header is not supported? If not, will look to create a PR for this.\r\n\r\nThe reason for looking at it was I am using prometheus to scrape metrics from a service (deployed within Istio), and currently the HTTP request scraping the metrics is being traced. Is there anything else I should try?\r\n\r\n",
